headline: Brookdale Incurs Loss in Q4 Due to Higher Costs, Shares Up 6%
summary: BKD's Q4 results reflect escalating general and administrative costs, partly offset by improved occupancy rates. It projects 2025 adjusted EBITDA within $430-$445 million.

headline: Insurers closed out 2024 on shaky footing
summary: Operating income fell for all but two major payers’ insurance divisions in the fourth quarter. And 2025 may be no better, after many insurers released outlooks suggesting medical costs will continue to rise.
